postcontent: The new EMP4 is cool, but the new model has both a longer slide and grip. Cool gun, but the original is a better fit under your shirt or inside your belt. If you are looking at this ad, you probably know how good the Springfield EMP feels in the hand and on the belt. If not, you should check it out. The EMP is not a 9mm mag and barrel stuck in a full size 1911 45, it's a 1911 pattern pistol engineered from the start as a 9mm. Mated with a 3 inch bull barrel, it's an ideal size for concealed carry. Still a factory mag, but it loads flush to the borrom of the grip. A real must have.Springfield provides a plastic OWB holster and dual mag holster, but you'll want others. I'm including a black leather OWB holster with a mag slot. Very comfortable.
